column1: #Text=Lockport is a city in the Niagara Frontier of New York .
#Text=Buffalo-Niagara International Airport is less than a 30 minute drive from Downtown Lockport .
#Text=Lockport is serviced by the Niagara Frontier Transportation Authority ( NFTA ) .
#Text=Lockport is a 30 minute drive east of Niagara Falls , NY down Route 31 .
#Text=It is best to rent a car .
#Text=In the summer Lockport has a tourism trolley .
#Text=The NFTA bus stops are not far from the downtown attractions .

#Text=boat rides are offered on the Erie Canal , with one proceeding upward through the modern locks for a short cruise , and returning to pass downstream under two lift bridges and then returning to the docks .
#Text=A museum is located in the old lock control structure and contains historic photographs , maps , engineering drawings , and machinery .
#Text=The Canal Discovery Center is housed in an old church about 100 yards to the west of the locks .
#Text=Lockport is home to the widest bridge in North America which spans the canal to the southwest of the locks .
#Text=The Lockport Caves tour can be taken near the locks .
#Text=The Niagara County Historical Society located at 215 Niagara Street in Lockport , NY .
#Text=It is a complex of buildings that together tell the story of Niagara County history .
#Text=100 American Craftsmen is an annual show of arts and crafts held at the Kenan Arena .
#Text=The arena is located on the historic Kenan Center campus .
#Text=Ida Fritz park plays host to the Taste of Lockport every August and to a Cruise Night every Monday during the summer .
#Text=Lockport is now the home of the Molson Canal Concert Series on Fridays in the summer .
#Text=The series brings national acts to the recently constructed Ulrich City Centre and events are free of admission charge .
#Text=Just outside of Lockport is The Niagara Wine Trail .
#Text=Lockport Cave & Underground Boat Ride , 2 Pine St ( NY 78 to Main St , left on Pine ) , ☏ +1716 438-0174 .
#Text=10 May - 18 May : Sa Su noon-4PM ; 24 May - 20 Jun : daily noon-4PM ; 21 Jun - 1 Sep : daily 10AM-5PM ; 2 Sep - 13 Oct : M - F 11AM 1PM 3PM 5PM , Sa Su 11AM-4PM .
#Text=This 70-minute walking tour starts with a viewing of the " flight of five " locks that gave the city its name .
#Text=A walk along the canal speaks to the industrial history of the area , and then it 's into the Lockport Cave , a man-made tunnel built to provide hydraulic power to those canalside industries .
#Text=A short boat ride takes you deeper into the tunnel before returning to end the tour .
#Text=A book on the Erie Canal at the Erie Canal Discovery Center or Lockport Locks and Erie Canal Cruises .
